{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"read"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"buffer","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sv","text":"UnsafeMutableRawPointer"},{"text":"!, ","kind":"text"},{"text":"count","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"cancellable"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV","text":"CancellableRef","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableRef"},{"kind":"text","text":"? = nil) "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"throws"},{"text":" -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"gssize","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:glibconfig.h@T@gssize"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Discussion","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If count is zero returns zero and does nothing. A value of ","type":"text"},{"code":"count","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"larger than "},{"code":"G_MAXSSIZE","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" will cause a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"invalidArgument"},{"type":"text","text":" error."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"On success, the number of bytes read into the buffer is returned.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"It is not an error if this is not the same as the requested size, as it","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"can happen e.g. near the end of a file. Zero is returned on end of file","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"(or if ","type":"text"},{"code":"count","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is zero),  but never otherwise.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The returned "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"buffer"},{"text":" is not a nul-terminated string, it can contain nul bytes","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"at any position, and this function doesn’t nul-terminate the "},{"code":"buffer","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cancellable"},{"type":"text","text":" is not "},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", then the operation can be cancelled by","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"triggering the cancellable object from another thread. If the operation"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"was cancelled, the error "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cancelled"},{"text":" will be returned. If an","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"operation was partially finished when the operation was cancelled the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"partial result will be returned, without an error.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"On error -1 is returned and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"error"},{"type":"text","text":" is set accordingly."}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Tries to read ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"count"},{"type":"text","text":" bytes from the stream into the buffer starting at"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"buffer","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". Will block during this read."}],"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/BufferedInputStreamRef","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/BufferedInputStreamRef\/InputStreamProtocol-Implementations"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/BufferedInputStreamRef\